thread.title: Magnitude 7.1 quake strikes east of Papua New Guinea island

title: Magnitude 7.1 quake strikes east of Papua New Guinea island
text: March 8, 2018 / 6:19 PM / in 15 minutes Magnitude 7.1 quake strikes east of Papua New Guinea island Reuters Staff 1 Min Read (Reuters) - An earthquake of magnitude 7.1 struck 135 km (85 miles) east of the town of Rabaul, on the eastern tip of Papua New Guineaâ€™s island of New Britain, at 3.39 a.m. on Friday, local time (1739 GMT on Thursday), the U.S. Geological Survey said. Although the quake was under the seabed at a relatively shallow depth of 10 km, the Pacific Tsunami Warning Center said there was no threat of a tsunami. A quake of magnitude 7.5 struck the rugged highlands of the Papua New Guinea mainland on Feb. 26, killing more than 100 people. Editing by Kevin Liffey and Andrew Roche
